GTA IV took a more serious turn for the series, but even as it told the tale of taciturn Niko Bellic it kept its trademark humour with characters like Brucie. A young, rich luxury automotive entrepeneur, Brucie loves partying, fast cars, slapboxing, and talking…and talking…and talking. He never shuts up, spouting off ridiculous boasts, nonsense schemes, and bad jokes.
